I do know the parses I've made with Bo4 and muzzle show a delay of 18.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 389<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 4:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: is muzzle worth 5 k ?</span><hr size=1> It depends, but I'd say it worth more if you had to. <br>
<br>
-This is the only summoned haste item, and you can give it out to (any?) other pet users.<br>
<br>
-An increase of 11% is more than just 11% more hits, it's also if I'm not mistaken, an 11% more chance to proc weapon procs.<br>
<br>
-Unlike Burn Out 4, there is no upgrade to this, or rather, this summon will be an upgrade to not only your cutrrent pets, but to all pets you ever have..<br>
<br>
-It's undispellable, like all of our summoned pet goodies.<br>
<br>
- Pet damage cannot be resisted like our spell damage can. Anything that adds to the pet makes you a more effective mage.<br>
<br>
- Think of it this way: When a melee looks at weapon upgrades, how much do you think he pays to get an 11% increase (whether it's lower delay, or more damage)?<br>
<br>
Any way I look at Muzzle is a must have spell. What plat price tag that carrries depends on your means, but if that plat you have isn't going to buy something that increases your power pretty well then buy Muzzle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liffthemage>Liff the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 4:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: is muzzle worth 5 k ?</span><hr size=1> NO fricken way is this spell worth 5k.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't buy it then if I knew what I know now.  I am a chaincaster.  I can't break that addiction.  So for me, it is worthless.  The only time I use it really is to give to necro pets.  <br>
<br>
If I was to rate its worth, I would say 200 to 800 plat for a grouping mage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2483<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 5:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: is muzzle worth 5 k ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>if I'm not mistaken, an 11% more chance to proc weapon procs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->So far as I know, procks are independent of delay.  Dexterity increases the chance of a prock, but nothing I am aware of increases the frequency.<br>
<br>
With all the new pet summons, the balance of power has shifted in favor of sustaining pets rather than chaining pets, and the muzzle is very good in this case.<br>
<br>
I am not sure I would pay 5K for it, but I would think about it if I did not have the spell and did not have a guild that loved me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 9:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: is muzzle worth 5 k ?</span><hr size=1> While Muzzle is a very usefull spell, you shouldn't pay 5k. An appropiate prize is between 500 and 1000 pp. I got mine for 500 and I see it all the time (on xev) for 1000 or less.<br>
<br>
<br>
nmee <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stubblekb>StubbleKB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: is muzzle worth 5 k ?</span><hr size=1> Well, I guess muzzle can effect the number of procs in an indirect way. It increases the haste of the pet, which makes the pet swing more, which may result in more procs. But it doesn't directly add any increased chance to proc. <p>-Stubble</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedwellerindarkness@themagicianstower>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 4:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: is muzzle worth 5 k ?</span><hr size=1> What I meant was that with more swings, and presumable each swing has a chance for a proc, that it seems to follow that you would get an 11% chance for more procs. Same percant chance per swing, but over all more swings per fight might mean more procs per fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc@themagicianstower>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1352<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 7:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Noonie is right</span><hr size=1> Ya haste does affect procing in a outside kinda way. With the new weapons, levels, pets the mask is truly worth it. Every time your pet or any melee for that matter swings they have a chance to proc. Now dex increases the change that they will proc on a given swing however having 11% more swings will increase proc rate around 11% just because you are swinging 11% more.<br>
<br>
