T have to hit).  So haste DOES increase the number of procs per unit time, because it increases the number of swings per unit time.  More swings (with the same chance of a proc) = more procs.<br>
<br>
But there is a very simple rule to use when looking at haste.  This includes ALL ranges of damage/delay and with or without procs.  Haste % increase is directly proportional to DPS increase.<br>
<br>
So, if it adds 11% haste, it adds 11% to melee DPS (including melee procs).<br>
